{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Defodio| type=Spell| features=Gouges channels in material| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Deathly Hallows/Chapter 26|''Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows'']]}}
== Overview ==
'''''Defodio''''', a gouging spell, is used to cut channels or grooves in solid material.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Hermione Granger|Hermione]] uses this spell to carve space into the tops of tunnels as the Trio escape from [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Places/Gringotts|Gringotts]] on the back of a [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Dragon|dragon]]. [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry]] and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Ron Weasley|Ron]] follow her lead, cutting away parts of the passages that the dragon is trying to get through as it finds its way out of the cellars of Gringotts.
== Analysis ==
It is interesting that spells are so very specific; it is noted that there are several different cleaning spells, [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Evanesco|Evanesco]] for inside containers, [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Scourgify|Scourgify]] for surfaces, and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Tergeo|Tergeo]] for dust. Here we see that there is a specific spell for gouging surfaces; while it is similar to the other destructive curses, like [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Reducto|the Reductor curse]] and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Deprimo|Deprimo]], it is not the spell that Hermione uses in this instance.
A large part of ability in [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Charms|Charms]], then, must be the ability to remember the specific spell that would provide the wanted effect, out of a list of possibly hundreds or thousands, along with the ability to associate the correct gestures and mental state with it.
== Questions == {{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Questions}}
