{{recipe}}
{{recipesummary||4|35 minutes}}
==Ingredients== *1 cup besan (Gram flour) *2 glasses buttermilk (a bit sour) *1 small onion, *1 piece garlic *1/4 inch of ginger *4-5 kadi patta *turmeric powder *salt, *4 red chilis *pinch of asafoetida *black mustard *oil for making pakoda
==Procedure== #Mix 1 cup besan (leave 1 spoon for kadi) with water,salt,turmeric powder and mix it for sometime so that mixture should just be like little less batter than cake mix. #Put oil in big pan and heat it. #Drop mixture in the pan with the help of round kind of spoon so that pakodas are round and fluffy.
For the kadi: #Mix butter milk, 1 spoon besan, turmeric powder, asafoetida, salt and mix nicely so that there are no lumps. #Cut onion in small pieces. #Heat a little oil. Put mustard seeds, garlic, ginger, kadipatta then onion and fry it until a little reddish. #Now mix the buttermilk mixture and put it in the fried mixture. Keep it on medium flame and continue mixing it until it starts bubbling. #Put in the pakodas and lower the heat and keep for some time. Close the lid and switch off the flame.
==Notes== Eat it with rice or roti, it will be nice. If you want to make it more spicy put garam masala and chilli powder in pakoda and butter milk mixture also.

===Problem compiling the code as shown===

I've gotten compilation errors with the code as provided (gcc 4.3.3).  The compiler wouldn't finish parsing the template.
By modifying the template to look like
<source lang="cpp">
template<typename Def, typename Inner = typename Def::type>
struct right_enum : Def
{
    typedef typename Def::type type;
    typedef Inner inner;
    inner v;
    right_enum(type v) : v(static_cast<type>(v)) {}
    operator inner () const {return v;}
};
</source>
I can get it to compile.  I have not gotten to full check this newer version.  --[[User:RhysU|RhysU]] ([[User talk:RhysU|talk]]) 14:36, 28 April 2009 (UTC)

: No need to test, the change you've made is correct, and what is already in the article is incorrect. (The compiler already knows that Inner is a typename because it is declared as such in the template.)

: I'll update the article now.

: [[Special:Contributions/121.210.170.141|121.210.170.141]] ([[User talk:121.210.170.141|talk]]) 04:11, 26 November 2009 (UTC)

== Non-member operators ==

=== Non-member operators for left-most argument conversions ===

Because of the current implementation, compilers cannot do automatic conversion of the left-most arguments included in comparison.

<source lang="cpp">
struct color_def {
  enum type { red, green, blue };
};
typedef safe_enum<color_def> color;

int main(void)
{
  color c = color::red;

  if (c == color::red) // this compiles seamlessly
    std::cout << "Working like a clockwork." << std::endl;

  if (color::red == c) // error: operator== is not defined for color_def::type
    std::cout << "Hooray, I've made it." << std::endl;
}
</source>

I'm using my own implementation that defines non-member operators, and it works. If we can agree on this, I can post my code here for revision.

--[[User:VedranOdGradista|VedranOdGradista]] ([[User talk:VedranOdGradista|talk]]) 12:32, 5 March 2012 (UTC)

