__NOTOC__
This text explores aspects of effective student organizations. Its primary focus is on clubs and organizations that exist on university campuses, are student focused, student operated and face particular organizational problems associated with student involvement. One of the major problems that these groups face is the loss of [[w:institutional knowledge|institutional knowledge]] when students in leadership positions graduate or leave the university. This wikibook aims to counter this loss of institutional knowledge by providing a record of the effective strategies that students are using to organize. 

The wikibook [[Managing Groups and Teams]] may serve as an excellent companion to this text, it offers a theoretically grounded and well detailed guide to effective leadership and management of groups. 

